When would you want to use a remote repository rather than keeping all your work
local?

when you want to publish code/information publicly for everyone to view or make private

Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git
automatically stay up-to-date with your remote repository?

    you may be beta testing and/or you want the ability to control information
    that is being pulled

Describe the differences between forks, clones, and branches.  When would you
use one instead of another?

    branches are used when wanting to add features, clones get information from the
    entire file/branch i. e. master file and creates a replica, forks are a replica
	of the entire repository of another profile from someone on github the information
	comes over as your own and you are able to make changes as if it were your own
	to continue coding

What is the benefit of having a copy of the last known state of the remote
stored locally?

    you're still able to make final changes and edits if necessary

